SVGAElement.summary: The SVGAElement interface provides access to the properties of an a element, as well as methods to manipulate them.

SVGAElementDownload.summary: The download property of the interface returns a string indicating that the browser should treat the linked URL as a download.

remarks.para: This property can be set, to change the URL's download value. It reflects the value of the download attribute.

blockquote.para: This value might not be used for download. This value cannot be used to determine whether the download will occur.

SVGAElementHash.summary: The hash property of the interface returns a string representing the fragment identifier, including the leading hash mark (#), if any, in the referenced URL.

remarks.para: This property can be set, to change the URL's fragment (ignores leading #).

SVGAElementHost.summary: The host property of the interface returns a string representing the hostname and port (if it's not the default port) in the referenced URL.

remarks.para: This property can be set, to change the URL's host and port.

SVGAElementHostname.summary: The hostname property of the interface returns a string representing the hostname in the referenced URL.

remarks.para: This property can be set, to change the URL's hostname.

SVGAElementHref.summary: The href read-only property of the returns an object reflecting the value of the href attribute, and, in certain cases, the {{SVGAttr("xlink:href")}} {{deprecated_inline}} attribute. It specifies the target URI associated with the link.

remarks.para: This property enables access to the URI set for a link within an SVG document.

SVGAElementHref.value: An indicating the value of the href attribute. Additionally, for elements defined to support it, it reflects the value of the {{SVGAttr("xlink:href")}} {{deprecated_inline}} attribute when the href attribute is not set.

SVGAElementHreflang.summary: The hreflang property of the interface returns a string indicating the language of the linked resource.

remarks.para: This property can be set, to change the URL's hreflang value. It reflects the value of the hreflang attribute.

SVGAElementInterestForElement.summary: CAUTION Non-standard The interestForElement property of the interface gets or sets the target element of an interest invoker, in cases where the associated {{svgelement("a")}} element is specified as an interest invoker.

remarks.para: See Creating an interest invoker for more details.

SVGAElementInterestForElement.value: An object instance, or null if the associated <a> element does not have a target element set.

SVGAElementOrigin.summary: The origin readonly property of the interface returns a string containing the origin of the URL â€” that is, its scheme, its domain and its port.

SVGAElementPassword.summary: The password property of the interface returns a string containing the password specified before the domain name.

remarks.para: This property can be set, to change the URL's password.

SVGAElementPathname.summary: The pathname property of the interface returns a string containing an initial / followed by the path of the URL, not including the query string or fragment.

remarks.para: This property can be set, to change the URL's pathname.

SVGAElementPing.summary: The ping property of the interface returns a string that reflects the ping attribute, containing a space-separated list of URLs to which, when the hyperlink is followed, POST requests with the body PING will be sent by the browser (in the background). Typically used for tracking.

remarks.para: This property can be set, to change the URL's ping value. It reflects the value of the ping attribute.

SVGAElementPort.summary: The port property of the interface returns a string representing the port component, if any, of the referenced URL.

remarks.para: This property can be set, to change the URL's port.

SVGAElementProtocol.summary: The protocol property of the interface returns a string representing the protocol component, including trailing colon (:), of the referenced URL.

remarks.para: This property can be set, to change the URL's protocol.

SVGAElementReferrerpolicy.summary: The referrerpolicy property of the interface returns a string specifying which referrer to send when fetching the URL..

remarks.para: This property can be set, to change the URL's referrerpolicy value. It reflects the value of the referrerpolicy attribute.

SVGAElementRel.summary: The rel property of the returns a string reflecting the value of the rel attribute of the SVG a element.

remarks.para: The rel attribute specifies the space-separated list of link types, the <list-of-Link-Types>, indicating the relationship between the target or resource represented by the a element and the current document. The property can get or set the rel attribute value.

SVGAElementRel.value: A string; the value of the rel attribute.

SVGAElementRelList.summary: The read-only relList property of the returns a live reflecting the space-separated string <list-of-Link-Types> values of the rel attribute of the SVG a element.
SVGAElementRelList.value: A live .Although the relList property itself is read-only in the sense that you can't replace the DOMTokenList object, you can still assign to the relList property directly, which is equivalent to assigning to its property. You can also modify the DOMTokenList object using the , , , and methods.

SVGAElementSearch.summary: The search property of the interface returns a string representing the URL's query string, if any, including the leading question mark (?).

remarks.para: This property can be set, to change the URL's query component.

SVGAElementTarget.summary: The SVGAElement.target read-only property of returns an object that specifies the portion of a target window, frame, pane into which a document is to be opened when a link is activated.

remarks.para: This property is used when there are multiple possible targets for the ending resource, like when the parent document is a multi-frame HTML or XHTML document.

SVGAElementTarget.value: An indicating the ending resource target that opens the document when the link is activated. See {{SVGAttr("target")}} for valid values.

SVGAElementText.summary: IMPORTANT Deprecated The text property of the interface returns a string that is a synonym for the property.

SVGAElementType.summary: The type property of the interface returns a string indicating the MIME type of the linked resource.

remarks.para: This property can be set, to change the URL's type value. It reflects the value of the type attribute.

SVGAElementUsername.summary: The username property of the interface returns a string containing the username specified before the domain name.

remarks.para: This property can be set, to change the URL's username.
